oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Kangaroo court skit
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a Kangaroo Court skit which was presented during the Sesquicentennial. There are men dressed up as law enforcement officers and one man dressed up as a judge. They are putting another man into stocks.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Theatrical productions; Stocks (Punishment)
